title: b'Britain to get consular access to Christian Michel soon'

title: b'In Bulandshahr violence that killed 2, top cop says cow slaughter key issue'

title: b"Red flag for Amit Shah's Bengal rath yatra from court, upset BJP to appeal"
description: b'The Calcutta High Court ordered that the BJP\xe2\x80\x99s West Bengal rath yatra cannot take place till the next date of hearing, January 9, when it would consider reports from the 24 districts through which the rally was to pass.'

title: b"Congress trying to save 'mama Michel': BJP launches new attack over VVIP chopper..."
description: b'A day after Prime Minister Narendra Modi brought up alleged AgustaWestland chopper deal middleman Christian James Michel\xe2\x80\x99s extradition at a poll rally to target the Congress, BJP spokesman Sambit Patra raised the political affiliation of the lawyers defending the British businessman.'

title: b'Turn the H-1B rule tweaks into an opportunity'

title: b'Viability, not production growth, is the biggest crisis facing farmers'
description: b'Price crashes lead to a decline in cultivation of a crop in the next season, this leads to a spike in prices leading to increase in cultivation in the next season. It could be a good idea to educate farmers about rationalising their expectations and hence future cultivation decisions in periods of scarcity.'

title: b'Why 2018 is critical for the Congress'
description: b'The recent assembly elections offer the Congress its best, and last chance, to build some momentum heading into the 2019 elections. If the Congress is unable to win atleast two major states, it stares at the real prospect of being a totally deflated army heading into the national polls'

title: b'Mama, I love you: 12-year-old scribbled on palm before suicide, teacher blamed'
description: b'Around 4 pm, when the mother returned, she discovered her daughter\xe2\x80\x99s lifeless body, a police officer said. A suicide note was also recovered. '

title: b'Why Team India can gain redemption Down Under'

title: b'The killing of the UP inspector points towards an institutional crisis'
